olive oil
1 stalk celery
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 packet garlic paste
1 tsp honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet diced bacon

• Thinly slice celery.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook diced bacon with beef & pork mince, until beef, pork and bacon is browned, 4-6 minutes. Drain excess oil.
• Add chermoula spice blend and garlic paste and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove from heat, add the honey and toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, celery, baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Spread chargrilled capsicum relish over tortillas, then top with slaw and Middle Eastern-spiced beef, pork and bacon.
• Drizzle over garlic aioli to serve. Enjoy!